&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of scale, massing, siting and design, represents an undesirable addition that would appear overly dominant in relation to the original dwelling, particularly when considering the cumulative impact of extensions. It therefore fails to respect the character and appearance of the original dwelling and terrace row, causing harm to each of these. The proposal thus fails to accord with the following policies which seek to ensure that development proposals are well designed and respect the existing character:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot; style=&quot;direction:ltr;unicode-bidi:embed;margin-top:0in;
 margin-bottom:0in&quot;&gt;
 &lt;li style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7pt;&quot;&gt;National Planning Policy Framework&amp;nbsp;(NPPF) (DLUHC, 2023)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7pt;&quot;&gt;Policy D4 of the London Plan (March 2021)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7pt;&quot;&gt;Policy CP3 of
     the&amp;nbsp;Local Development Framework Core Strategy (July 2010)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7pt;&quot;&gt;Policy BP11 of the&amp;nbsp;Local Development Framework Borough Wide
     Development Plan Document (March 2011)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7pt;&quot;&gt;Policies SP2, DMD1 and DMD6 oof&amp;nbsp;The London Borough of Barking and Dagenham’s Draft
     Local Plan: (Regulation 19 Submission Version, December 2021)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7pt;&quot;&gt;Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (February 2012)&lt;/li&gt;
 
 
 
 
 &lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot; style=&quot;direction:ltr;unicode-bidi:embed;margin-top:0in;
 margin-bottom:0in&quot;&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of scale and massing, would&amp;nbsp;result in 
disproportionate additions over and above the size of the original building. It therefore constitutes inappropriate development within the Green Belt, with no very special circumstances put forward. As such, the proposal is considered to cause undue harm to the Green Belt, contrary to the following policies:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;National Planning Policy Framework&amp;nbsp;(NPPF) (DLUHC, 2023)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Policy G2 of the London Plan (March 2021)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Policy CM3 of
the&amp;nbsp;Local Development Framework Core Strategy (July 2010)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Policy SP6 of&amp;nbsp;The London Borough of Barking and Dagenham’s Draft
     Local Plan: (Regulation 19 Submission Version, December 2021)&lt;/li&gt;
 
 
 &lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot; style=&quot;direction:ltr;unicode-bidi:embed;margin-top:0in;
 margin-bottom:0in&quot;&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
